==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fanon
<hw>Fan"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>fanon</ets>,
LL. <ets>fano</ets>, fr. OHG. <ets>fano</ets> banner cloth, G.
<ets>fahne</ets> banner. See <er>Vane</er>, and cf. <er>Fanion</er>,
<er>Gonfalon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A term applied to
various articles,</def> <specif>as:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
peculiar striped scarf worn by the pope at mass, and by eastern
bishops.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A maniple.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>fannel</asp>, <asp>phanon</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fan palm</ent>⟦br⟧
